Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.51,0:01:42.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\1c&HFF00FF&\b1}第5季　第5集
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.88,0:00:03.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最初  宇宙是一片黑暗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In the beginning, there was darkness,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.11,0:00:05.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,紧接着一声巨响  混沌初开\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and then, bang, giving birth
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.94,0:00:07.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,时间  空间和物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to an endless, expanding existence
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.73,0:00:09.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,开始不断膨胀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of time, space, and matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.40,0:00:13.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每天  我们都在解密这神秘莫测\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Every day, new discoveries are unlocking the mysterious,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.29,0:00:12.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\fn微软雅黑\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}彗星撞击木星
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.12,0:00:14.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\fn微软雅黑\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}发现新行星
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.99,0:00:16.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,令人疯狂的极端之地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the mind-blowing, the deadly secrets
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.50,0:00:17.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\fn微软雅黑\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}流星撞地球
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.70,0:00:19.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of a place we call the Universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.64,0:00:24.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们是人类在外太空的眼和耳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They are humanity's eyes and ears in deep space,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.83,0:00:29.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,探测火星上的平原  土星卫星上的间歇喷泉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}exploring the plains of Mars, the geysers of Saturn's moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.96,0:00:32.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,和遥远恒星炽烈的表面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the blazing surfaces of distant stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.38,0:00:37.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们就是空间探测器  机器人探测器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They are space probes: robotic explorers
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.78,0:00:41.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在是人类在星际间的化身\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that are now humanity's interstellar avatars.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.72,0:00:43.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们所能到达的地方和见到的事物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They can go places and see things
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.49,0:00:45.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是我们在地球上永远到不了也看不到的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that we could never do from here on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.87,0:00:49.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,空间探测器分散分布在太阳系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Space probes fan out across the solar system,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.64,0:00:54.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,传回的数据让我们对已知的事物有所改观\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}returning data that change everything we thought we knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.45,0:00:59.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果我们能在银河系的其他地方找到生命的存在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If we could find indigenous life elsewhere in our galaxy,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.76,0:01:03.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这将是人类历史上最伟大的发现之一了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it would be one of the greatest discoveries in the history of humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.91,0:01:07.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,探测器迎面撞击冰冷的彗星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Probes collide head-on into icy comets,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.19,0:01:10.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,拍摄宇宙的边缘之地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}photograph the edge of the universe itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.56,0:01:13.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,甚至在其他星系中寻找行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}even seek planets in other solar systems.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.12,0:01:21.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们处在一个探索发现类地行星的黄金时代\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We're at a golden age in the search and discovery of earth-like planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.05,0:01:23.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,通过揭示各种奥秘\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A new generation of robotic explorers
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.75,0:01:28.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,新一代机器人探测器正在重新定义这个星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is redefining the galaxy itself by unlocking secrets:
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.32,0:01:31.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,空间探测器的奥秘\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}secrets of the space probes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.05,0:01:49.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,此时此刻\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At this very moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.81,0:01:52.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,距地球数百万英里之外的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}millions of miles from the earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.48,0:01:57.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,人类正在取样  测量  摄影\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}human beings are sampling, measuring, photographing
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.58,0:02:01.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,甚至吸进另一个世界的尘埃和气体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and even sniffing the dust and gases of other worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.08,0:02:04.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但不是亲身经历\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But not in person.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.81,0:02:09.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙的环境非常不利于人类生存\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The environment of space is very hostile to people.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.66,0:02:11.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,极端温度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's got extremes of temperature,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.89,0:02:13.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}艾米·美因茨\N美国国家宇航局/喷气推进实验室
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.63,0:02:14.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,极端真空  高辐射区\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}extremes of vacuum, high radiation fields,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.76,0:02:17.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所有这一切都非常不适合人类居住\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}all kinds of things that are really inhospitable to human life.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.50,0:02:24.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,机器人代替我们的眼和耳去执行任务\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our eyes and ears are robotic proxies sent on missions
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.11,0:02:27.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,探索太阳系甚至更远处的奥秘\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to discover the secrets of our solar system and beyond.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.13,0:02:32.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们是空间探测器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They are space probes
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.51,0:02:36.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能在恶劣之境和危险之地生存\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and they were built to survive the hostile atmospheres and perilous worlds
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.58,0:02:38.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是人类所办不到的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that mankind cannot.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.34,0:02:42.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们的航空探测器能够在困境中生存\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our space missions are able to survive these difficult environments
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.64,0:02:45.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所到之处  所做之事都是我们望尘莫及的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and they can go places and do things that we could never dream of without them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.64,0:02:50.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一些探测器  如哈勃空间望远镜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some probes, like the Hubble Space Telescope,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.63,0:02:54.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在地球轨道上自在漂浮  另外一些\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}float comfortably in earth's orbit, while others,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.03,0:02:59.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如2005年的"深度撞击号"  指定执行自杀性任务\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like Deep Impact in 2005, are ordered on kamikaze missions
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.41,0:03:02.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将人造卫星探测器直接撞向彗星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to smash satellite probes into comets.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.71,0:03:06.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还有一些用于行星探秘\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Others are sent to uncover the secrets of planets
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.65,0:03:12.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如火星  木星  土星  或其卫星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like Mars, Jupiter, Saturn, or their moons,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.34,0:03:16.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,通过在轨道上进行图像分析\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}imaging and analyzing them from orbit
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.54,0:03:20.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,登陆进行地表探测或取样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and landing on their surfaces to explore or dig for samples.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.26,0:03:23.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,探测器用来回答基本问题\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our probes are used to answer fundamental questions
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.92,0:03:25.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,包括行星的构成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about planetary composition,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.92,0:03:27.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}凯文·P·格雷瑟尔\N美国国家宇航局/喷气推进实验室
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.93,0:03:29.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大气成分  地质情况  大气运动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}atmospheric composition, geologic, atmospheric processes,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.11,0:03:32.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以及它们与地球的相似及不同之处\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}how are planets both similar to and different than earth
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.99,0:03:36.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,更为重要的问题是  有无生命存在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the big-picture question: is there life?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.48,0:03:45.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,寻找外星生命始于两千年前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The hunt for life on other worlds began over 2,000 years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.13,0:03:48.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那时希腊天文学家们开始关注行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when Greek astronomers began gazing at planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.69,0:03:53.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,21世纪  人类终于准备好去寻找外星生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In the 21st century, humanity is finally poised to find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.31,0:03:56.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,向太阳系甚至更远处发射探测器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Sending out probes into the solar system and even beyond,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.69,0:03:58.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是一项长期任务的一部分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it is part of a long-standing mission
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.88,0:04:02.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们不仅必须了解地球上的我们自己\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we've had to understand, not just ourselves here on earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.89,0:04:05.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}克利福德·约翰逊\N南加利福尼亚大学
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.58,0:04:05.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还必须了解太阳系中其他星球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but the rest of the solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.35,0:04:06.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在某种程度上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And in some ways,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.76,0:04:09.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,探索过程让我们对自己有了更多的了解\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that quest helps us learn more about ourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.74,0:04:11.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,比如人类起源这个话题\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in terms of where we may have come from
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.83,0:04:13.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是否有与地球上的环境类似\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and whether there are any other examples
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.64,0:04:16.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,的其他地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of the environment we see here on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.91,0:04:22.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最近一次探索以超高分辨率的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The latest quest begins with an ultra-high-resolution
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.05,0:04:24.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,数字红外路线图为起点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}digital infrared road map.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.40,0:04:29.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,2009年12月14日\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}On December 14, 2009,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.79,0:04:33.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,三角洲2号火箭向离地球300英里外的轨道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a Delta II Rocket delivered a small package into orbit
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.30,0:04:35.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,发射了一个小型探测器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}300 miles above the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.85,0:04:38.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它被称为"智慧号"\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's called W.I.S.E.,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.36,0:04:43.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将创建迄今为止最为精细的宇宙红外图像\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it's creating the most detailed infrared photograph of the universe to date.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.43,0:04:46.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"智慧号"是广范围红外线观测探测器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}W.I.S.E. is the wide-field infrared survey explorer,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.95,0:04:48.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是个小体积望远镜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it's a small-size telescope,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.47,0:04:50.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,直径约为40公分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about 40 centimeters in diameter.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.48,0:04:52.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,相当于我手臂下面这里的尺寸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So that would sort of fit under my arm here.
