Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.95,0:04:58.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,探测距地球最近的星球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Everything from the earth's closest neighbors,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.45,0:04:59.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,小行星  彗星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the asteroids and the comets,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.88,0:05:02.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,甚至宇宙最远方的红外波段\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to the most distant parts of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.73,0:05:05.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,哈勃空间望远镜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Unlike the Hubble telescope
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.50,0:05:09.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一般观测可见光到紫外光的波段\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that generally images wavelengths, visible to ultraviolet light,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.28,0:05:13.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"智慧号"则勘测太空中的红外光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}W.I.S.E. probes the universe using infrared light.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.44,0:05:17.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,人类对于红外线的感觉是热\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Human beings perceive infrared as heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.23,0:05:19.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,阳光照在我们皮肤上产生的热感\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When we feel the sun's warmth on our skin,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.52,0:05:23.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其实是来自于阳光中的红外线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}what we're really sensing are the infrared rays coming from the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.39,0:05:26.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我坐在这里就散发着红外线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I'm pouring out infrared light as I sit here,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.32,0:05:27.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们可以利用红外线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we can use infrared
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.51,0:05:29.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来寻找类似温度的物体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to look for things that are sort of similar temperature,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.69,0:05:31.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,例如  小行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like, for example, asteroids.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.65,0:05:35.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们还能利用红外线来寻找整个宇宙中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We can also use infrared to look for the most distant galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.00,0:05:36.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最遥远的星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the entire universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.51,0:05:42.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些遥远的星系很多都不能被可见光谱勘测到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Many of these distant galaxies can't be perceived in the visible light spectrum.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.40,0:05:47.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"智慧号"红外望远镜成了一副魔力眼镜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The W.I.S.E. infrared telescope becomes like a magic set of glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.20,0:05:51.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像消防员用红外护目镜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, just like a firefighter uses infrared goggles
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.22,0:05:54.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在着火的大楼里透过烟雾救人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to look through smoke in a burning building to find people,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.20,0:05:57.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,天文学家用红外线能透过尘云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}astronomers can use infrared to see through dust clouds
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.13,0:05:59.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,寻找其内部正在形成的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to look for forming stars in their cores.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.33,0:06:02.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是呈现这些隐藏的热源信号\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But revealing these hidden heat signatures
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.92,0:06:05.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,首先需要一个深冷环境\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}first requires an extreme deep freeze.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.66,0:06:09.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"智慧号"的四百万像素望远镜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}W.I.S.E.'s 4 million-pixel telescope
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.50,0:06:15.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只能拍摄比其温度低的物体的红外图像\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}can only photograph infrared images if the telescope is colder than the objects it searches for.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.87,0:06:18.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以  我们需要确保\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, we need to make sure
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.55,0:06:21.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没有因为我们望远镜的热度而产生的盲点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that we're not blinded by the heat of our own telescope.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.07,0:06:23.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们在"智慧号"上用了一箱固态氢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}On W.I.S.E., we use a tank of solid hydrogen
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.40,0:06:25.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它在接近绝对零度下凝固\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that's frozen near absolute zero,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.54,0:06:28.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这样就能冷却我们的望远镜和设备\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and this keeps our telescope and our instrument cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.91,0:06:31.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像个装满冰的冷却器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Just like a cooler full of ice,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.52,0:06:33.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"智慧号"上的固态氢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the frozen hydrogen on board W.I.S.E.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.48,0:06:35.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最终将升华消失\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is eventually going to sublimate away.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.81,0:06:37.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当我们用完所有的固态氢时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When we run out of all of the hydrogen ice,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.98,0:06:40.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,望远镜和设备将变热\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the telescope and the instrument will warm up to the point that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.65,0:06:42.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,直至我们无法勘测\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we'll no longer be able to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.27,0:06:47.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,冷却到零下447华氏度[-266摄氏度]\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Frozen to minus 447 degrees Fahrenheit,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.55,0:06:50.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,固态氢只能持续十个月\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the hydrogen can only last for about 10 months.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.35,0:06:55.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,到那时  大约150万张图像\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}By that time, some 1.5 million photographs
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.70,0:06:59.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将组成一幅巨大的太空合成图\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}will create a giant composite picture of the heavens:
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.54,0:07:03.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一本揭示了新世界的宇宙地图集\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a cosmic road atlas that can reveal new worlds
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.22,0:07:05.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,供未来的空间探测器设立目标\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for future space probes to target,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.77,0:07:09.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很可能是探测有外星生命的世界\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}potentially, worlds with alien life forms.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.56,0:07:14.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是若要找距地球好几光年的外星生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But if we are to find alien life many light-years from earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.68,0:07:17.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们需要一条关键线索来指引我们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we'll need a critical clue to lead us there.
