Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.35,0:07:28.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们对寻找液态水的兴趣主要在于\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One of the main reasons we're interested in finding
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.35,0:07:29.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}艾力克斯·菲利潘科\N美国加州大学伯克利分校
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.68,0:07:32.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们真的想知道在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}liquid water is that we really would like to know,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.45,0:07:35.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳系的其他地方是否存在生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is there life elsewhere in the solar system?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.04,0:07:39.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,众所周知  地球上的生命需要水来维持\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Life on Earth, as we know it, needs water to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.51,0:07:40.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,需要水来形成生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It needs water to form.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.34,0:07:44.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们希冀在其他星球发现生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We hope to find life elsewhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.35,0:07:49.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,作为生命存在的指路明灯  首先需要找的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and a signpost for life might be first finding a place
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.84,0:07:52.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或许就是有水  液态水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where there's water, liquid water.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.66,0:07:57.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,纵贯人类历史\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Throughout human history,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.42,0:07:59.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尚未有证据指出宇宙中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there was no proof that liquid water existed
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.80,0:08:02.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,除地球外还有地方存在液态水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}anywhere else in the universe besides Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.85,0:08:06.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,直至97年一台先进的空间探测器到达土星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}until a sophisticated space probe arrived
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.57,0:08:10.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,执行探索任务才颠覆了我们的认知\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on a mission of discovery to the planet Saturn in 1997.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.76,0:08:15.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,卡西尼号耗时4年  行程4亿英里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Cassini traveled 400 million miles and took four years
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.01,0:08:18.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,才到达土星  开始历时数年的探测行动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to begin a multi-year spy mission
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.45,0:08:21.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以揭示土星的奥秘\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to uncover the secrets of Saturn.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.12,0:08:24.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,卡西尼号探测器前往土星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When the Cassini probe got to Saturn,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.12,0:08:26.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}劳拉·丹利\N格里菲斯天文台
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.53,0:08:27.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它不仅只是研究该行星及其所有的卫星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}not only did it study all the moons and the planet in particular,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.38,0:08:30.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而且还会脱离飞船  变换轨道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but then it went out of the plane, changed its orbit,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.23,0:08:32.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,由上至下的观测土星环\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and could look down on the Rings.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.18,0:08:36.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其中一环尤其吸引卡西尼号科学家的注意\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One ring in particular attracted Cassini scientists.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.95,0:08:42.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们知道土星最外环  E环\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We knew that Saturn's outermost ring, the "E" Ring,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.26,0:08:45.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是由极其细小的微米级冰粒组成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was made of very small micron-sized ice particles.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.07,0:08:50.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,微米级的冰粒子在太空中无法长存\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Micron-sized ice particles don't last long in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.65,0:08:53.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们知道在土星系统中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We knew there was a source of stuff in the Saturn system
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.67,0:08:55.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,必定存在形成E环的供源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that was creating the "E" Ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.29,0:08:57.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们当时猜测是土卫二\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We guessed it was Enceladus.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.26,0:09:00.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当卡西尼号接近土卫二时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When Cassini approached the moon, Enceladus,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.98,0:09:04.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,目击了一种宇宙现象  证实了水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it witnessed a cosmic phenomenon and confirmed that water
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.67,0:09:08.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,的确同样是另外一个世界的关键成分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was indeed a key ingredient on another world.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.70,0:09:13.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,卡西尼号宇宙飞船发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Cassini spacecraft has detected water
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.59,0:09:16.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土卫二地表下存在水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}under the surface of Enceladus,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.45,0:09:19.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它观测到从土卫二\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the way it was detected was that these geysers
