Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.94,0:09:36.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,源源不断的冰粒形成了土星的E环\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The constant stream of water ice particles feeds Saturn's "E" Ring,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.03,0:09:39.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它提醒了我们如果在太阳系内\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}An icy reminder that if liquid water exists
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.89,0:09:42.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,遥远的星球上存在液态水的话\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on remote planets in our own Solar system,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.00,0:09:45.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那么在宇宙的其他地方也会有的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it might be found elsewhere in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.84,0:09:49.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而卡西尼号对水源的搜寻尚未结束\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But Cassini's hunt for liquids wasn't over.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.75,0:09:52.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它还将利用其灵敏的仪器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it would have to use its sensitive instruments
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.40,0:09:56.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,穿透土星系统内的其他大气层\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to penetrate other atmospheres of the Saturnian system.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.29,0:10:00.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,卡西尼宇宙飞船携带了12组科学仪器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Cassini spacecraft has 12 science instruments.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.78,0:10:04.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其中4组是我们所说的光学遥感仪器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Four of them are what we call optical remote-sensing instruments.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.03,0:10:09.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们观测的波长带等同或稍宽于人类肉眼\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They see in the wavelength of band that humans see or just outside of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.09,0:10:12.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙飞船安装的滤镜可以穿透\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The spacecraft has filters that are designed to peer
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.15,0:10:15.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,层层迷雾探测掩盖下的地表\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}through that haze and see through to the surface below.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.44,0:10:18.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,卡西尼号内的仪器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Cassini's instruments are designed
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.21,0:10:20.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,利用各种工具来收集情报信息\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to gather intelligence with different tools,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.87,0:10:24.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,与人类运用自身的各种感官大同小异\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}much the same way that humans use our different senses.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.03,0:10:29.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,卡西尼的直接遥感器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Cassini's direct and remote sensors
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.27,0:10:32.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,首先开始研究的是土星的泰坦卫星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}first began studying Saturn's moon, Titan,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.11,0:10:36.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有人相信这里存在着液态水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a place that some believed could contain liquid water.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.39,0:10:39.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,泰坦比水星还要巨大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Titan is bigger than the planet Mercury,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.10,0:10:41.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有浓密的大气层\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with a dense atmosphere,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.93,0:10:44.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,甚至比地球的大气层还要浓厚\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}thicker than even the earth's atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.91,0:10:50.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当1980年旅行者号空间探测器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In 1980, when the Voyager space probe flew by on its way
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.84,0:10:52.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在去往太阳系外层途径此地时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to the outer solar system,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.40,0:10:56.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,拍摄的照片暗示了存在着另一种液体现象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}its photographs hinted at another liquid phenomenon.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.61,0:10:58.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,旅行者号宇宙飞船向我们展示了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What the voyager spacecraft
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.91,0:11:02.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它的大气层里充满了碳氢化合物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}told us is that that atmosphere is filled with hydrocarbons...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.82,0:11:06.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,甲烷  乙烷  产生了浓厚的光化雾霾\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Methane, ethane, that create a thick photochemical haze.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.61,0:11:10.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,旅行者号飞船无法看透那层雾霾\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The voyager spacecraft couldn't see through that haze.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.80,0:11:14.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当25年后卡西尼号开始研究泰坦时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When Cassini began studying Titan 25 years later,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.32,0:11:19.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它还发射了颗名为惠更斯的卫星监控探测器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it also launched a satellite spy probe called Huygens.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.25,0:11:23.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,该探测器穿过泰坦的碳氢大气层\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the probe penetrated the thick hydrocarbon atmosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.67,0:11:25.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在地表着陆\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and landed on Titan's surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.85,0:11:30.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,卡西尼及其着陆器的发现令人震惊\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What Cassini and its lander found was shocking.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.15,0:11:35.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最初  卡西尼和惠更斯观测到了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Very early on, Cassini and Huygens had seen hints
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.21,0:11:38.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,泰坦地表液体存在的细微迹象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of the evidence of fluids on the surface of Titan.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.34,0:11:40.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最终  它们发现了碳氢化合物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Eventually, they found hydrocarbons.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.54,0:11:43.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,找到了碳氢湖  有些比五大湖还宽广\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They found hydrocarbon lakes, some larger than the Great Lakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.74,0:11:47.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是首次在太阳系内地球以外\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These are the first open bodies of fluids
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.18,0:11:49.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,发现露天的液体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}found in the Solar system outside of Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.76,0:11:54.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,典型的类地暴风雨使得湖水充盈\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The lakes are filled by classic earth-like rainstorms.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.84,0:12:00.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而在泰坦  雨滴并非是水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But on Titan, the raindrops are not H2O,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.78,0:12:03.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而是缓缓而下液态甲烷\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but slow-falling liquid methane.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.02,0:12:07.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球上的甲烷大都处于气体状态\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A lot of the methane on Earth is in the gaseous state.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.27,0:12:11.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,称为天然气  其实是源自腐烂的有机体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's called natural gas, in fact, and it comes from decaying organisms.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.59,0:12:15.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有机体不停的分解  形成天然气\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And they're still decomposing and they form this natural gas,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.18,0:12:18.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,成为地球上可以使用的燃料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which we can use as a fuel here on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.41,0:12:22.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,泰坦液态甲烷甚至能养育简单的生命体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Titan's liquid methane world could even harbor simple life forms,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.45,0:12:27.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像在地球深海发现的单细胞生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}much like the single-celled life found in the depths of Earth's oceans.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.64,0:12:32.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那里存在的种种可能真是让人兴奋不已\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So there's a lot of excitement about the possibilities that could be out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.30,0:12:36.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,远方的行星系统是活跃的  有趣的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Planetary systems out there are active, interesting,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.37,0:12:41.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,包罗万象的  生命的形式同样多姿多彩\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and very varied, and we know that life can take many different forms.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.44,0:12:45.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或许能在遥远的围绕者其他恒星运转的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Life might be found on distant planets
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.47,0:12:46.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,星球上发现生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}orbiting other stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.52,0:12:48.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,问题是如何到达彼方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The problem is getting there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.63,0:12:54.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而新研制的超级引擎利用其类似\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But a new super engine with a propulsion system similar
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.38,0:12:55.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,微波技术的推进系统\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to microwave oven technology
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.88,0:13:02.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,正随时准备为深入外太空之旅推波助澜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is preparing to turbocharge deep space travel.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.10,0:13:13.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,空间探测器能无畏的前往人类未履之地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Space probes can boldly go where no human has gone before.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.06,0:13:15.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而数十年来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But for decades,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.37,0:13:18.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家一直与一个严酷的现实抗争\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}scientists have wrestled with a harsh reality:
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.06,0:13:21.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,空间探测器也会出师未捷\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Space probes can fail.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.52,0:13:25.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每一次的成功  都建立在半个世纪以来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Every one that succeeds is built upon a half century
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.86,0:13:28.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,失败的任务和破灭的梦想之上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of failed missions and shattered dreams.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.94,0:13:33.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太空探测史从20世纪60年代开始\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The history begins in the 1960s
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.04,0:13:38.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,美国宇航局首次尝试前往地球最近的邻居\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with NASA's first attempts to reach Earth's nearest neighbors.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.99,0:13:41.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,首批徘徊者号探测器是用于拍摄\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our first Ranger probes were designed to take images
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.29,0:13:43.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,月球以及硬着陆前的路线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of the Moon and a route to smashing into the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.81,0:13:47.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最初的6枚探测器完全偏离了月球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And our first six rangers missed the moon entirely,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.81,0:13:47.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}凯文·P·格拉齐尔\N美国航天航空局/喷气推进实验室
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.87,0:13:49.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是我们很快就吸取了教训\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but we learn quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.66,0:13:52.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,徘徊者号探测器失败后数月\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And a few months after the Ranger probes,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.45,0:13:55.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们成功的发射了太空船飞过金星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we sent a successful spacecraft to fly past Venus.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.19,0:14:00.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,1962年美国探测器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In 1962, the American probe,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.25,0:14:04.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,水手2号是首个飞经金星的太空船\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Mariner 2 Is the first spacecraft to fly past Venus.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.37,0:14:10.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它揭示了我们最近的邻居跟我们截然不同\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It reports that our nearest neighbor is no place like home.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.47,0:14:15.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们曾以为金星与地球如同孪生姐妹\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We used to think that Venus might be like a twin sister of Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.22,0:14:17.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有着炎热潮湿的丛林\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with hot steamy jungles.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.22,0:14:18.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}艾力克斯·菲利潘科\N美国加州大学伯克利分校
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.45,0:14:19.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而空间探测器告诉我们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Well, the space probes taught us that,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.87,0:14:22.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉  金星有着天壤之别\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}sorry, Venus isn't like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.72,0:14:27.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,美国宇航局的探测器证实金星太炎热了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The NASA probe proves that Venus is too hot
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.35,0:14:30.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其气压太大无法承载任何生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and its pressure is too great to support any life.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.52,0:14:35.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而1970年首个登陆金星的探测器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But in 1970, the first probe to land
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.51,0:14:39.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,却并非来自美国  而是来自苏联\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on the planet isn't American, but Soviet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.66,0:14:42.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,金星探测器有个内壳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Venera probes had an inner shell,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.03,0:14:44.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,钛金属构成的内舱非常牢固\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}an inner hull of titanium that was tough.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.58,0:14:46.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能在一段时间内经受住\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It could withstand, at least for a while,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.72,0:14:51.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,金星地表毁灭性压力和酷热\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The crushing pressure and the intense heat of the Venus surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.82,0:14:56.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此早期抵达金星的探测器在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So the early probes to Venus got destroyed
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.02,0:14:58.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,仅仅半小时不足一小时内被摧毁了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in just half an hour or under an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.32,0:14:59.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在被气压碾碎前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They were able to take data
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.45,0:15:02.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们只能提供短时间的数据\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for only a short amount of time before they got crushed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.11,0:15:05.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但探测器在损坏前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the data sent back
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.40,0:15:09.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,送回的数据准确而惊人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}before Venera's destruction is precise and surprising.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.81,0:15:14.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,金星的表面如同地狱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Conditions on the surface of Venus are hellish.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.83,0:15:18.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,温度大约为华氏860度[460摄氏度]\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The temperature is about 860 degrees Fahrenheit.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.74,0:15:20.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,温度相当高\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's really, really high.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.18,0:15:23.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,煮沸的开水仅有华氏212度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I mean the boiling point of water is 212 degrees
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.19,0:15:28.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,铅熔化的温度亦稍稍低于860度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and lead melts at a temperature slightly lower that 860.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.97,0:15:31.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以如果你把铅放到金星表面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, you'd have molten lead on the surface of Venus
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.54,0:15:33.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就会的到熔融的铅\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if you had lead there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.11,0:15:34.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,真是个恶劣的环境\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's a really bad place to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.48,0:15:39.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,金星是探索科学家的极端环境试验场\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Venus is an extreme training ground for probe scientists.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.64,0:15:42.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但还有一个更远大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But there is a more distant
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.14,0:15:43.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,更艰巨的目标\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and difficult goal,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.01,0:15:47.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还有一种星的极端环境比金星更具破坏力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One whose extremes are even more destructive than Venus:
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.08,0:15:49.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,带外行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Outer Planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.32,0:15:50.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\fn微软雅黑\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}带外行星:  木星  土星  天王星  海王星和冥王星
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.48,0:15:53.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,仅有大型火箭不足以还到达那里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And getting there requires more than just a big rocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.20,0:15:56.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,空间探测器的最大问题之一\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One of the biggest problems with space probes
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.56,0:15:58.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是拥有足以飞抵目的地的的燃料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is having enough fuel to get where you're going.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.86,0:16:00.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你发射火箭  花费很多燃料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you do a rocket burn, you burn a lot of fuel.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.56,0:16:02.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}特拉维斯·斯·泰勒\N物理学家
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.05,0:16:02.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,保持一组火箭发射器运转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And if you keep doing a bunch of rocket burns,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.91,0:16:04.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会使你用尽燃料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you're gonna run out of fuel,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.05,0:16:05.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你的探测器就无用了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and then your probe is dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.09,0:16:08.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但存在一个解决方法\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But there is a solution
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.71,0:16:11.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,利用宇宙结构  万有引力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}built into the fabric of the cosmos: gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.38,0:16:14.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,六十年代早期  研究发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In the early '60s, it was discovered
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.65,0:16:18.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,人们可以利用行星的引力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that we can use the gravity of the planets
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.11,0:16:19.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来辅助航天器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to assist a spacecraft,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.44,0:16:20.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,使其加速\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to speed it up to fling it
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.97,0:16:22.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将其送入外太阳系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}further out into the solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.75,0:16:25.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这开辟了对于外太阳系的探索\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That opened up the outer solar system to exploration.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.77,0:16:29.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这项技术被称为  重力助推\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The technique is called gravity assist,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.73,0:16:31.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是一个运用行星体的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a virtual engine that harnesses
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.90,0:16:34.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,巨大万有引力的虚拟引擎\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the immense gravity of planetary bodies
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.00,0:16:37.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在预定轨道上对航天器进行助推\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to assist a spacecraft on a planned trajectory.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.48,0:16:46.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,打棒球与借助重力的过程颇似\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Hitting a baseball is a lot like a gravitational assist.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.66,0:16:48.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,空间探测器到达一颗行星附近\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The space probe comes into a planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.53,0:16:49.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,被其引力捕获\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it gets caught by the gravity
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.79,0:16:51.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,改变自己的方向\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and redirected in another direction,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.39,0:16:53.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像用球棒击打棒球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}just like hitting a baseball with a bat
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.22,0:16:55.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,引导球转向其他方向\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it directs the baseball in another direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.28,0:16:59.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当球棒撞击棒球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When the bat collides with the baseball,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.34,0:17:04.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它就改变了棒球的运动方向\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it changes the baseball's direction of motion
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.20,0:17:06.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并且推动棒球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it can propel that baseball
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.17,0:17:09.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,达到比撞击前更快的速度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with a much greater speed than what it originally had.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.24,0:17:16.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,通过利用行星的引力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}By harnessing the gravitational pull of planets,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.24,0:17:19.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,美国宇航局可以将探测器送出驻留轨道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NASA has been able to hit probes out of the park
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.04,0:17:21.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,送至外行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and to the Outer Planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.89,0:17:26.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,卡西尼号太空船的本垒打\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Cassini's home-run journey
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.00,0:17:27.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,飞跃了一亿七千万英里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}covered 170 million miles
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.92,0:17:31.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,到达土卫泰坦的甲烷湖泊\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to the methane lakes of Saturn's moon, Titan.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.97,0:17:37.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,离开了重力助推  这艘在地球上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Without those gravity assists, this spacecraft,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.07,0:17:39.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,重十二吨的航天器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which weighs 12 tons in earth's gravity,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.11,0:17:41.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是不可能到达外太阳系的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}never would have made it to the outer solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.11,0:17:42.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们没有足以直接\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We don't have a booster big enough
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.51,0:17:44.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,发送将它到土星的助推器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to send it to Saturn directly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.38,0:17:47.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果没有内行星的引力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We would not have explored Saturn
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.41,0:17:49.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们不能探索土星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}were it not for the gravity of the inner planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.86,0:17:53.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在  二十一世纪的空间探索\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, 21st century space exploration
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.66,0:17:54.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,准备派遣探测器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is poised to send probes
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.97,0:17:58.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,到外行星以外的遥远恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}beyond the outer planets to distant stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.75,0:18:01.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但重力助推\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But gravity assist
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.15,0:18:02.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不足以令我们到达那里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}doesn't have the power to get us there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.87,0:18:07.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,进入深空探测看起来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Traveling into deep space requires propulsion
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.54,0:18:11.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,显然需要科幻小说中的动力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that seems to come straight out of science fiction:
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.27,0:18:12.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,离子推进器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the ion drive.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.28,0:18:18.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,离子引擎就像一个小型直线加速器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Ion engines are like a mini linear accelerator.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.34,0:18:19.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你向后加速离子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You accelerate ions out the back,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.91,0:18:21.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,航天器飞向相反的方向\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the spacecraft goes the opposite direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.98,0:18:27.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,离子引擎的推力  非常非常小\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That ion engine has very, very low thrust,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.30,0:18:30.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但它一次可以运转数月  并且最终\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but it operates for months at a time, and eventually,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.19,0:18:32.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,使航天器的速度越行越快\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}gets the spacecraft up to faster and faster speeds.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.88,0:18:36.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,离子引擎通过诸如氙气的惰性气体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The ion engine replaces the chemical fuel
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.76,0:18:39.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,取代了化学燃料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with an inert gas like xenon.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.78,0:18:44.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,氙气提供了电荷  或称电离\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The xenon is given an electrical charge, or ionized.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.71,0:18:47.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,之后电子场加速离子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}An electric field then accelerates the ions
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.58,0:18:49.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,离子从航天器后端飞出\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}out the back of the spacecraft,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.74,0:18:51.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,推动航天器前进\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}propelling it forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.95,0:18:55.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,离子推进器和大多数火箭引擎不同\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Ion propulsion is not like most rocket engines.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.82,0:18:58.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个普通化学火箭引擎推动自己的方式\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A standard chemical rocket engine propels itself
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.87,0:19:01.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,像一把双管十二毫米口径猎枪\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like a double-barreled 12-gauge shotgun.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.47,0:19:04.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,猎枪实际上就是一个化学推力引擎\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This shotgun is actually a chemical rocket engine,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.91,0:19:07.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,和航天飞机的主发动机很像\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}just like the space shuttle main engines.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.32,0:19:09.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我坐在地球上的一辆小车上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I'm sitting on earth on a dolly track.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.71,0:19:11.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,问题是  猎枪能否提供\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So the question is, is there enough thrust
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.51,0:19:13.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,足以克服轮子和轨道间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from the shotgun to overcome
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.07,0:19:15.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,的摩擦力的推力呢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the friction between the wheels and the track?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.96,0:19:20.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,单枪射击可以使小车移动六英尺\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A single blast moves the dolly about six inches.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.05,0:19:23.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,第二枪使运动状态持续\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A second blast keeps the momentum going.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.34,0:19:27.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在  用一个较小的武器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But now, replace the big double-barrel shotgun
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.60,0:19:29.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,替换大型双管猎枪\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with a smaller weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.12,0:19:31.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在我拿着雷帽弹步枪\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, I have a .22 rifle.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.77,0:19:33.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这和猎枪有些许区别\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's a little different than the shotgun.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.51,0:19:36.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,猎枪以一个相当温和的速度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The shotgun shot many pellets out
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.26,0:19:39.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,射出许多子弹\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at a fairly moderate velocity.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.12,0:19:40.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,步枪高速射击出\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The rifle shoots a small pellet out
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.43,0:19:42.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一颗很小的子弹\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at very high velocity.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.00,0:19:43.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,区别就是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, the difference is that
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.45,0:19:45.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这把更像离子引擎\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}this is more like an ion engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.97,0:19:51.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雷帽弹的反冲使小车移动了不到一英寸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The .22 recoil moves the dolly less than an inch.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.98,0:19:54.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,连发射击使他移动了稍多一点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Multiple shots move it slightly more.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.69,0:19:56.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但如果我们身处太空中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But if we were in space,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.15,0:19:59.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雷帽弹就会像离子引擎\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the .22 would be just like the ion engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.69,0:20:02.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它会开始慢慢推动我们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It would start pushing us slowly
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.38,0:20:03.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最终使我们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and eventually build up,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.28,0:20:04.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,达到一个很高的速度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}till we reached a really high velocity.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.50,0:20:08.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,通过微小推力不断汇集变大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}By compounding tiny thrusts through the vast,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.32,0:20:10.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在无摩擦力的太空深处\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}frictionless depths of space,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.10,0:20:14.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,离子引擎可以推动探测器数年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the ion engine can propel a probe for years.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.10,0:20:16.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\fn微软雅黑\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}加拿大理论天体物理研究所二次太空着陆计划
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.25,0:20:17.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这项技术意味着\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The technology could mean the end
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.14,0:20:20.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大型火箭推进器在空间探测上应用的终结\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for massive rocket boosters in space probe travel.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.86,0:20:23.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,化学燃料存在问题\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Chemical fuels are a problem
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.69,0:20:24.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为它们很低效\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because they're pretty inefficient.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.06,0:20:27.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们很重  体积很大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They weigh a lot. They have a lot of mass.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.02,0:20:29.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并且你需要把它们运到太空\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And you have to transport all that stuff out there,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.87,0:20:33.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这意味着发射宇宙飞船的火箭\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that means the rockets that launch the spacecraft
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.67,0:20:36.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,需要更多能量  也更昂贵\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}have to be even more powerful, even more expensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.73,0:20:39.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,轻量级离子引擎\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Lightweight ion engines
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.63,0:20:41.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,已经通过了外太空试验\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}have already passed the test in outer space.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.02,0:20:43.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们在九十年代末\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They powered the deep space 1 probe
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.81,0:20:45.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,推助了深空一号探测器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&} in the late 1990s,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.62,0:20:48.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并在最近推动了日本宇宙航空研究开发机构\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and recently propelled the probe, Hayabusa,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.38,0:20:51.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,研制的隼鸟号号探测器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of the Japanese aerospace exploration agency
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.39,0:20:53.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,帮助它着陆到一个小行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and helped it land on an asteroid.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.53,0:20:56.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,离子引擎会彻底\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Ion engines will completely
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.58,0:20:58.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,改变深空探索\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}change deep-space exploration
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.34,0:21:00.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为我们不需要很多燃料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because we can go a lot more places
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.34,0:21:01.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}劳拉·丹利\N格里菲斯观察员
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.77,0:21:03.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就可以到达更多的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}without having to carry a lot of fuel.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.21,0:21:06.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并且最终  我们可能以更快的速度达到那里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And we can get there, in the end, faster,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.21,0:21:08.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这取决于我们要去哪儿\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}depending on where it is we're going.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.59,0:21:12.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们可能会去的地方之一\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One of the places we may be going
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.83,0:21:14.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是我们的邻近行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is our planetary neighbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.25,0:21:19.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,目前  欧洲航天局的火星快车探测器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Currently, the European space agency's mars express probe
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.13,0:21:22.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,保持了六个月从地球到达火星的速度冠军\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}holds the Earth-to-Mars speed title at six months,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.57,0:21:26.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但一个先进的离子引擎\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but one advanced ion engine
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.10,0:21:28.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有望打破这个纪录\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is expected to shatter that record.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.61,0:21:32.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,离子引擎可以使到火星的时间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}An ion engine could cut the travel time to Mars
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.21,0:21:34.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,缩短至数周\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}down to just a mere few weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.71,0:21:38.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,五周到达火星仅仅是一个开始\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Five weeks to Mars is only the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.48,0:21:44.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,离子驱动器下一步将加快它的速度一百倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The next step in ion drives will amp up its speed as much as 100 times faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.25,0:21:48.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这被称为Vasimr\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's called Vasimr,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.19,0:21:51.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可变比脉冲等离子体火箭的缩写\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}an acronym for variable specific impulse magneto-plasma rocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.63,0:21:57.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,等离子体火箭的离子引擎增添了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Vasimr's ion engine gets an added
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.64,0:22:01.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,射频发生器和二级推进器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}radio frequency generator and a second stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.11,0:22:05.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很重要的一点是它的工作原理有点像微波炉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One of the key things is it works kind of like a microwave oven.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.31,0:22:08.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,微波炉发出电磁波\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Just like a microwave beams electromagnetic energy
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.32,0:22:10.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来加热食物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into the food to superheat it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.13,0:22:12.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,等离子体被加热后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As the plasma gets superheated,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.52,0:22:14.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它获得了多得多的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}then it's got way more energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.33,0:22:16.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,加热过的等离子体贮存在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's got this really strong magnetic field that takes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.27,0:22:17.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,探测器的很强的磁场中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that superheated plasma
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.46,0:22:20.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并以极快的速度从其尾部喷射出来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And shoots it out the back end at really high velocities.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.81,0:22:26.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,离子能够被加热到大约一百万度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The ions can be superheated to about one million degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.34,0:22:32.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那足以将一个探测器送到我们太阳系之外很远\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's enough to send a probe far beyond our solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.64,0:22:38.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随着火箭技术的发展\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As rocket technology advances,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.93,0:22:42.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,深空探索的大门正在打开\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the gates of deep space are swinging open to exploration.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.82,0:22:45.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们需要的只是目的地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All we need is a destination.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.47,0:22:48.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个空间探测器此刻\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One space probe is right now
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.46,0:22:50.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,正在宇宙中仔细寻找那个目的地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}scanning the heavens for that destination:
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.29,0:22:55.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个新的地球  很有可能一种新的生命形式\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a new earth, and possibly a new form of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.13,0:23:08.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,空间探测器正站在天文学最古老追求之一的最前沿\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Space probes are on the cutting edge of one of astronomy's oldest quests:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.98,0:23:13.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,寻找另一个地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the search for another earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.38,0:23:17.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在  新一代的机器人探测器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, a new generation of robotic explorers
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.10,0:23:20.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,找到了太阳系外行星的证据\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}seeks evidence of extrasolar planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.16,0:23:22.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们正在寻找它们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And we're finding them.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.09,0:23:26.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳系外行星简单来说\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}An extrasolar planet is simply
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.14,0:23:29.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}杰佛里·马尔西\N美国加州大学伯克利分校
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.14,0:23:29.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就是一颗绕另一颗恒星运转的行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a planet that orbits another star.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.78,0:23:32.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们太阳系有八大行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We have eight major planets orbiting our sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.43,0:23:34.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而太阳是一颗典型的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and our sun is a typical star.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.27,0:23:37.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,几个世纪以来一直存在的一个问题是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And so a question that has loomed for centuries is
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.58,0:23:41.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是否有行星围绕我们在夜空中看到的星星运转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}whether there are planets that orbit the stars that we see at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.04,0:23:45.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,自伽利略时代开始\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Since the days of Galileo,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.00,0:23:47.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家们就相信在天空中的亿万颗星中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}scientists have believed there must be other planets
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.73,0:23:50.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一定存在其他行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}among the billions of stars in the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.30,0:23:54.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但对太阳系外行星的探寻\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the quest for extrasolar or exoplanets
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.15,0:23:58.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,直到伽利略之后四百年才得以成功\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}wasn't successful until 400 years after Galileo.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.63,0:24:02.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一九九五年  在仅仅离地球五十光年的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In 1995, in the Pegasus constellation,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.88,0:24:05.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,飞马星座\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}just 50 light-years from earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.29,0:24:08.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家们发现了第一颗真正的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists discovered the first true
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.21,0:24:11.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳系外行星  飞马座51b\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}extrasolar planet, 51 Pegasi b.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.86,0:24:14.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它仅仅是通过间接的线索发现的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was found only through indirect clues.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.28,0:24:18.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们只有通过一种"恒星摇摆法"\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We were only being able to find these extrasolar planets
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.28,0:24:19.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}特拉维斯·S·泰勒\N物理学家
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.24,0:24:20.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,才能找到这些太阳系外行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}using a technique called star wobble.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.35,0:24:22.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果有一颗像木星一样的大行星存在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you have a big planet like a Jupiter out there,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.39,0:24:25.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它会引起恒星的运动出现摇摆\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it would cause the star's motion to wobble.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.98,0:24:28.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但你不能直接说它就在那里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But you couldn't really sort of directly tell it was there.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.33,0:24:31.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也称为多普勒效应\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Also called the Doppler effect,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.69,0:24:34.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,摇摆是通过望远镜发现的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The wobble is observed through a telescope.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.76,0:24:37.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果恒星的光波有规律地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If the star's light regularly shifts
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.15,0:24:40.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,反复发生红移和蓝移\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}toward red or blue wavelengths and then back again,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.74,0:24:44.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那么围绕其运行的行星一定是引起光波偏移的原因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Then an orbiting planet must be causing the light to shift.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.07,0:24:51.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在过去的十多年  天文学家很幸运地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In the last decade or so, astronomers have been extremely lucky
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.63,0:24:55.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,发现了围绕其他恒星运行的上百颗行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to find hundreds of planets around other stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.52,0:24:58.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但我们发现的行星是巨行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the planets we've been finding are the large ones:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.37,0:25:00.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,像木星  土星和海王星那种\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Jupiters, the Saturns, some Neptunes.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.81,0:25:03.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们还不能够发现类似地球大小的行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We have not been able to find the earth-like planets,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.72,0:25:04.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果它们存在的话\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if they're out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.99,0:25:09.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,人类已经发现了数百颗太阳系外行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are now hundreds of verified extrasolar planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.94,0:25:13.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但它们中存在离地球足够近可以供人类探索的吗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But are any of these planets close enough for mankind to explore?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.47,0:25:18.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来自宾夕法尼亚州伊利的安娜贝尔·C\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's what Annabelle C. From Erie, Pennsylvania,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.59,0:25:23.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,向《宇宙解密》这样问道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}wanted to "Ask the universe," when she texted us...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.01,0:25:28.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,利用当今最先进的推进系统\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How long would it take for a space probe reach the nearest explanet?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.56,0:25:31.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,空间探测器要花多久才能到达最近的系外行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Using theest propulsion available today?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.12,0:25:34.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,安娜贝尔  很有意思的问题\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Annabelle, that's a really interesting question,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.70,0:25:36.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而事实上  没有既定的答案\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And, in fact, there's no set answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.97,0:25:38.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,使用今天的技术\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Using today's technology,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.75,0:25:43.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,空间探测器花大约十万年才能到达另一颗恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A space probe could reach another star in about 100,000 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.44,0:25:47.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,已知最近的太阳系外行星距地球10.5光年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The nearest known exoplanet is about 10 1/2 light-years away,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.34,0:25:49.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但有可能存在离地球更近的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But there might be a more nearby one,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.46,0:25:54.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或者我们可以在不久的将来改进推进技术\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or we might improve space propulsion technology in the near future.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.05,0:25:57.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以在相对不久的将来  也许我们能够\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So maybe we could get that down to about 10,000 years
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.56,0:25:59.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,把时间缩短到大约一万年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the relatively near future,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.95,0:26:02.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但对于现在来说  五万到二十万年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But something like 50,000 to 200,000 years
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.53,0:26:04.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是一个比较好的答案\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is a good answer for right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.35,0:26:11.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,寻找类地行星意味着到宇宙更深处探索\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Finding the earth-like planets means looking deeper into the cosmos,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.09,0:26:13.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,去寻找更模糊和更遥远的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at dimmer and more distant stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.58,0:26:17.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一种革命性的观察遥远恒星的技术\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A revolutionary method of watching these dim stars
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.53,0:26:20.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有可能会很快找出第一颗类地行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}could soon pinpoint the first new earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.43,0:26:23.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种技术被称为凌日法\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's called the transit technique,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.33,0:26:27.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种技术在行星绕过\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it offers a dead giveaway that an orbiting planet
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.42,0:26:31.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们视角下的恒星盘面时发现行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is crossing between the star and our viewpoint from earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.01,0:26:37.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们假设这个反射镜是恒星的盘面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, let's imagine this reflector is like the face of a star
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.05,0:26:41.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而在反射镜前面飞行的昆虫就像那颗行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and a bug flying in front of that reflector is like the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.41,0:26:44.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随着虫子围绕着反射镜前飞过时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As the bug goes in front of and around this reflector,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.76,0:26:47.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它会挡住反射镜一部分的光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it will block a little bit of the light from the reflector,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.62,0:26:49.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就同一颗行星运转时经过\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}just as would happen when a planet crosses
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.79,0:26:51.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,恒星前面时发生的情况一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in front of a sun-like star.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.98,0:26:55.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,光的减弱程度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The amount of dimming
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.25,0:26:59.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,往往小于恒星发出光强度的千分之一\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is often less than 1/10 of 1% of the star's light output.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.50,0:27:03.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很难注意到  但对于一个在宇宙中探索的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Barely noticeable, but it's more than enough
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.05,0:27:07.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,拥有千里眼的空间探测器来说已经很足够了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for one far-sighted space probe that's now scouting the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.33,0:27:11.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们很想知道宇宙中是否存在一颗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We'd love to know if there's another earth-like planet
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.46,0:27:13.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}艾米·美因茨\N美国国家宇航局/喷气推进实验室
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.22,0:27:13.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,类似地球的行星  如果有的话\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}out there somewhere, and the Kepler mission
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.15,0:27:15.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,开普勒计划大有可能找到它\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has a good chance of being able to see it if there is one.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.24,0:27:20.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,卡普勒号宇宙探测器是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Kepler space probe is the powerful eye
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.68,0:27:23.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家们用以发现类地行星的强有力工具\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}scientists will use to find the earth-like planets,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.95,0:27:27.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如谚语说的大海捞针\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the proverbial needles in the haystack.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.31,0:27:33.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,探测器的望远镜使用九千五百万像素的摄像机\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The probe's telescope is using a 95-megapixel camera
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.17,0:27:35.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来观察经过的行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to watch for the transiting planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.37,0:27:40.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,开普勒计划用所谓的"凌日法"\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Kepler mission is using the so-called transit technique
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.13,0:27:42.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来寻找新的太阳系外行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to search for new extrasolar planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.69,0:27:43.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,使用凌日法\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}With the transit technique,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.10,0:27:46.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,开普勒号探测器能够观察成千上万的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Kepler is watching thousands of stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.43,0:27:48.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,捕捉它们在行星经过时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Waiting for their light to slightly dim
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.38,0:27:50.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,亮度的轻微减弱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When a planet passes in front of the star.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.59,0:27:56.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,银河系中有几十亿颗恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The milky way is composed of billions of stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.80,0:27:59.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也可能有几十亿颗类地行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And potentially, billions of earth-like planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.57,0:28:03.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能都找到一颗类地行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The odds of finding one earth
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.52,0:28:06.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,围绕某颗恒星运转的几率很低\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}orbiting one particular star are very low.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.00,0:28:10.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以  开普勒会同时日夜不停地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, Kepler will train its unblinking eye
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.76,0:28:13.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,观测数千颗恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on many thousands of stars at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.49,0:28:17.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我这有张光盘用来代表一个行星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Here I have a DVD to represent a planetary system
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.62,0:28:21.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其恒星在中间  一颗行星在外围绕它运转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with the star in the center and a planet going around the outside,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.22,0:28:22.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当然  大部分时间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And of course, most of the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.02,0:28:25.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,该行星系同我们的视线平行\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the planetary system is tilted to our line of sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.93,0:28:27.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以随着行星的运转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And so, as the planet goes around,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.84,0:28:31.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它永远不会经过恒星前面  挡住星光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it never crosses in front of the star, blocking the starlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.94,0:28:33.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但如果我们幸运的话\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But if we're lucky,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.56,0:28:36.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能够看到行星的轨道面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the orbital plane of the planet is seen edge on,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.98,0:28:39.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当行星运转经过恒星前面时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}then the planet crosses in front of the star,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.48,0:28:42.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,挡住了部分光线  使恒星变得暗淡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}blocking some of the starlight, and dimming the star.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.39,0:28:43.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以  你得观察数万\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And so, you have to be watching
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.71,0:28:46.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,甚至数十万的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}tens or even hundreds of thousands of stars
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.62,0:28:48.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,才能有幸捕捉到一些行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to be lucky enough to catch a few planets
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.82,0:28:51.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,刚好运行在恒星前面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that happen to cross right in front of the star.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.02,0:28:55.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,全世界在等待的同时  开普勒号探测器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As the world waits, kepler watches
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.43,0:28:58.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每时每刻都在关注着遥远的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the distant stars moment by moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.48,0:29:00.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但如果它真的找到一颗新的地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But if it does find a new earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.14,0:29:03.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们能够真正意义上地发现什么呢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What can we actually find out about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.47,0:29:05.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它看上去会像什么\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What will it look like?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.84,0:29:08.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那里会有生命吗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Could there be life?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.68,0:29:12.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一旦开普勒发现像地球一样的行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Once Kepler finds earth-like planets,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.65,0:29:15.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我非常肯定它会发现的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and I'm fairly sure it will be successful,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.86,0:29:16.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,下一步就是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the next thing will be
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.91,0:29:19.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,试图分析来自那颗行星的光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to try to analyze the light from that planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.58,0:29:21.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个地球上有哪些化学成分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What's the chemical composition of this earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.80,0:29:23.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它有含氧的大气层吗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Does it have an oxygen atmosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.17,0:29:25.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还是只有二氧化碳或甲烷\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Or is it just carbon dioxide or methane?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.20,0:29:30.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这颗行星有大陆和海洋吗  表面有水吗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Does the planet have continents and oceans, water on the surface?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.43,0:29:36.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,目前我们还没有这样的技术\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Currently, we don't have the technology
