Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.53,0:35:41.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,胶体内更多的秘密被发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}An even more bizarre secret is discovered trapped in the gel,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.00,0:35:44.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,甚至飞得最远的空间探测器都还没有\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}particles that even the farthest-reaching space probes
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.91,0:35:49.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,收集到的粒子  真正来自其他太阳的物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}haven't yet gathered: the actual material from other suns.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.74,0:35:52.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我相信它们已经找到了一些尘粒\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I believe they have found some dust particles
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.19,0:35:58.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好像是来自于太阳系外  来自其他恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that appear to come from outside our solar system, from other stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.19,0:36:00.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些尘粒从那些恒星流出来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Because they have solar winds themselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.63,0:36:03.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为它们有自己的太阳风\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the dust particles are flowing away from those stars
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.81,0:36:06.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其中的一些正好进入了太阳系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And some of them happen to come into our solar system
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.23,0:36:09.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,被星尘探测器捕获\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and they get captured by the Stardust probe.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.14,0:36:13.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们第一次捕获了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We have captured for the first time,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.57,0:36:16.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来自其他恒星的星尘\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}literally, stardust from other stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.67,0:36:19.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太神奇了  太神奇了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's amazing. That's amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.47,0:36:26.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来自怀尔德2号彗星的星尘一直被研究至今\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The stardust analysis from Comet Wild 2 continues to this day
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.93,0:36:29.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可以帮助我们更深刻地理解\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and could yield even more insight into the origins
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.60,0:36:32.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们这个宇宙小角落的起源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of our tiny corner of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.91,0:36:37.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你想知道我们的太阳和行星是如何形成的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you want to understand how our sun and planet were formed,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.15,0:36:38.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}劳拉·丹利\N葛瑞菲斯天文台
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.24,0:36:41.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你就得理解我们是由哪些物质构成的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you need to understand the material out of which we were formed.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.18,0:36:44.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是想更好的了解宇宙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But a better understanding of our universe
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.53,0:36:47.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不应从遥远的恒星微粒着手\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}may come not from particles from distant suns,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.26,0:36:50.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而应从离我们最近的恒星开始\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But from the star closest to our home.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.65,0:36:56.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一艘探测器正等待发射  完成一次人类从未设想过的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A revolutionary probe is awaiting a launch date to fly headlong
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.43,0:37:00.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,革命性探索  飞往太阳系最热的区域\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into the hottest region that man has ever attempted to explore.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.11,0:37:11.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在  空间探测器穿梭翱翔于银河中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Space probes now soar through the galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.76,0:37:16.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,探寻火星  金星  外太空巨星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to explore the mysteries of Mars, Venus, the outer giants,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.10,0:37:20.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,遥远的外部行星甚至最远的那些星球的秘密\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the distant exoplanets and the farthest stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.23,0:37:27.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可我们自己星系的太阳仍有尚未解开的谜题\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But our own home star still has its unsolved mysteries.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.52,0:37:30.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这很快就会不同了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's about to change.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.00,0:37:34.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,之前的观测只覆盖了一些小区域  而不是整个太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Previously we looked at small areas, not the whole disk
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.14,0:37:36.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}托德·霍克斯马\N斯坦福大学
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.51,0:37:37.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或者说我们的观测时间有漏洞  经常三天打鱼\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or we've had gaps in our coverage where we've looked for a day
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.24,0:37:38.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,两天晒网\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or we've not looked for a day,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.18,0:37:40.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或者只花一天中的部分时间观测  而没有持续观测\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we've looked for part of day, but not the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.52,0:37:43.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是我们第一次有机会  全面观测太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So this is really our first chance to look at the sun as a whole star.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.35,0:37:50.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\fn微软雅黑\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}2010年2月11日
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.37,0:37:51.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一艘高科技太阳探测器驶抵太空    准备就绪\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A high-tech solar probe arrives in space, locked and loaded.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.36,0:38:02.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它的任务是  对太阳进行全天候高清彩色观测\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Its mission: watch the sun 24/7 in high-definition color
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.83,0:38:07.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并通过一兆的带宽向地球传输图片\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and transmit mega broadband images back to earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.32,0:38:10.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳动力学观测卫星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The solar dynamics observatory
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.61,0:38:13.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,拍摄的太阳照片  具有极高的分辨率\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}takes images of the sun in very high resolution,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.01,0:38:15.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}劳拉·丹利\N格里费斯天文台
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.01,0:38:16.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,极高的清晰度  和各种波长\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}high definition, in many wavelengths,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.45,0:38:19.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可以这么说  它在拍摄太阳的电影\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and essentially, it takes movies of the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.44,0:38:23.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它配备了四架高清望远镜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Using four HD telescopes,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.73,0:38:28.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,SDO发射的探测器架起一条永不间断的高清信道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the SDO transmits an unblinking hi-def-like channel to earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.37,0:38:32.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它向地球上载的科学数据\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}uploading 50 times more science data
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.00,0:38:34.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是NASA历史上其它探测任务获得数据的五十多倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than any probe mission in NASA history.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.82,0:38:38.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能看到第一手图像资料  真是让人兴奋\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was really exciting to look at some of the first images.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.41,0:38:42.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们看到的是  一个地方的细微特征\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What we saw was very small features in one place
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.20,0:38:44.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对其它地方造成了重大影响\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}having a big effect someplace else.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.24,0:38:47.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此  我们可以观察到一些发生在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So we could see something near the center of the disk,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.37,0:38:49.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,接近太阳系  太阳中心的现象与\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}center of the sun, and you could see the connection
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.71,0:38:53.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,发生在十万二十万英里之外的现象之间的联系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}between that and what was happening 100,000, 200,000 miles away.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.04,0:38:59.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,高等光学仪器通过10种不同波长的光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The advanced optics watched the sun in 10 different
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.00,0:39:03.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,观测太阳  其中包括远紫外线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}light wavelengths, including the extreme ultraviolet.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.63,0:39:05.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种波长的光极度有害\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This wavelength is so deadly
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.52,0:39:09.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,要是没有地球上空大气层的过滤它\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that without earth's upper atmosphere to filter it,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.25,0:39:11.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,人在海边晒一天就足以致命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a day at the beach would be fatal.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.36,0:39:14.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们最终的目标是观察太阳内部\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our eventual goal is to look inside the sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.40,0:39:16.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,看清在它表面之下  进行着怎样的活动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to see what's happening below the surface:
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.90,0:39:18.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,比如太阳内部有怎样的流动  怎样的运动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}what the currents are, what the motions are,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.52,0:39:20.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以及它们是如何联系在一起  组成一幅波澜壮阔的画面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and how that all ties together in a big picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.89,0:39:28.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,SDO将被用做探测器  日震学磁像仪\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The SDO will activate a sensor, the helioseismic magnetic imager,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.99,0:39:28.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\fn微软雅黑\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}SDO 日震与磁成像仪
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.73,0:39:31.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它能透过太阳炙热的表面  探测下面的事物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that can see through the scorching solar surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.66,0:39:34.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,日震与磁成像仪\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The helioseismic and magnetic imager:
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.70,0:39:36.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,运用声波探测太阳的内部\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we're using sound waves to probe inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.85,0:39:40.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像我们探测地震时用的方法\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Just like we do in a seismic way for earthquakes,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.73,0:39:43.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们通过太阳内部的声波\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we can use sound waves inside the sun to look and see
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.77,0:39:45.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,了解内部发生的一切\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}what's happening inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.36,0:39:48.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们尝试通过检测声波反射出太阳表面时的振动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So we look at the vibrations as they bounce off the surface
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.27,0:39:50.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,弄清太阳里正发生的一切\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and then try and figure out what's happening inside the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.14,0:39:55.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家们最热切想解开的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's this inner core, the solar dynamo,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.29,0:39:57.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是太阳的发动机  太阳内核的秘密\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that scientists most want to demystify.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.93,0:40:00.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,高能物质从这里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}From here come the unpredictable,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.82,0:40:03.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,毫无预兆地喷涌而出\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}violent eruptions of high-energy material
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.62,0:40:05.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,威胁着地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that can threaten the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.24,0:40:08.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些物质都带着电荷\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, that material is charged,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.31,0:40:11.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,常常形成所谓的日冕物质抛射\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}often in the form of what's called a coronal mass ejection.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.28,0:40:13.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}克利福德·约翰逊\N南加利福尼亚大学
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.71,0:40:15.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是大量以带电粒子形态存在的物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's a huge amount of material in the form of charged particles.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.77,0:40:21.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那些带电粒子抵达地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Those charged particles arrive here at earth
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.44,0:40:23.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,与地磁场相互作用\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and interact with our magnetic field.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.15,0:40:26.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果能靠得足够近  对这种活动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you can get close enough to do direct measurements
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.89,0:40:28.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,进行直接的测量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on that sort of activity,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.18,0:40:31.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们就能更好理解这些现象的原理\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we'd better understand how those processes work.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.31,0:40:34.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,接近行星体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Getting close to planetary bodies
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.27,0:40:37.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是半个世纪以来空间探测器一直在进行的工作\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is something space probes have been doing for half a century.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.55,0:40:42.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可要让探测器接近太阳  无异于自杀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But getting a probe close to the sun is a suicide mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.79,0:40:44.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,真是这样的吗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Or is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.01,0:40:49.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,预计在2015年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scheduled for launch in 2015,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.78,0:40:51.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳探测器+\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Solar Probe Plus will fly
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.51,0:40:57.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将径直飞入太阳两百万度的日冕  并免于毁灭\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}directly into the sun's 2-million-degree corona and survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.86,0:41:00.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳探测器+将到达离太阳很近的位置\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Solar Probe Plus will get very close to the sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.71,0:41:03.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}艾力克斯·菲利潘科\N美国加州大学伯克利分校
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.97,0:41:03.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大概在八或九个太阳半径之内\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}within eight or nine solar radii from the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.10,0:41:05.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,作为对比\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, for comparison,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.04,0:41:08.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球离太阳中心有两百个太阳半径的距离\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the earth is 200 solar radii from the center of the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.00,0:41:12.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这就意味着   太阳探测器+会被日冕浸没\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, Solar Probe Plus is gonna be immersed within the corona.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.84,0:41:17.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,日冕是这个我们称之为太阳的恒星  神秘的组成部分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The corona is a mysterious part of the star we call the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.32,0:41:21.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尽管日冕离日核较远\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Though farther from the sun's core,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.33,0:41:23.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但实际上  它比太阳表面的温度高\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's actually hotter than the sun's surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.33,0:41:27.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可要是一个人能到达那的话\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But if a human were to somehow get there,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.83,0:41:30.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那的寒冷会让他们大吃一惊\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they'd get a frigid surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.78,0:41:34.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,日冕的温度非常高  有几百万度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The solar corona is very hot, millions of degrees in temperature.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.27,0:41:38.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也就是说  粒子在飞速运动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That means the particles are moving around very, very rapidly.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.82,0:41:41.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,于是你会想  要是陷入日冕\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So you might think that if you were immersed in the corona,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.48,0:41:42.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就会被烧焦\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you'd get burned.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.80,0:41:44.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可是那的粒子的数量极少\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But there are so few particles,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.61,0:41:47.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此  通过碰撞转移到体内的总能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that the total amount of energy being transferred to a body
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.87,0:41:51.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,比辐射入体内的总能量少\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is less than the amount of energy being radiated.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.69,0:41:54.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,实际上  如果有一块性能优异的隔热板\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, in fact, you would freeze if you were immersed
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.75,0:41:58.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能保护你避免太阳的照射\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the solar corona, as long as you had a good heat shield
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.10,0:42:01.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那么一进入日冕区域  你就会冻僵\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}protecting you from the disk of the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.05,0:42:04.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳探测器+会装备上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Solar Probe Plus will come equipped
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.40,0:42:07.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一块轻型泡沫碳隔热板\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with a lightweight carbon-foam heat shield,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.00,0:42:10.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,使得探测器不管是在热浪\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}allowing it to survive the massive heat,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.65,0:42:14.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还是冻结效应的影响下  都能以接近室温的温度运行\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the freezing effect, and even operate near room temperature.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.89,0:42:18.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳探测器+完成任务之时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When it completes its mission, Solar Probe Plus
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.84,0:42:22.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将向我们展现太阳磁场的构造\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}will reveal the structure of the sun's magnetic Fields
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.34,0:42:25.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,探索日冕的高温来源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and explore the flow of solar energy
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.57,0:42:30.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并且孕育了地球生命的太阳能量流动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that heats the sun's corona and makes life on our planet possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.27,0:42:35.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们必须记住  太阳是离我们最近的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's important to remember that the sun is the nearest star.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.33,0:42:38.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,说真的  研究太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So really, it's important to study the sun
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.67,0:42:40.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在我们对宇宙所有恒星的研究事业中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as part of the entire enterprise
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.96,0:42:43.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是一个意义重大的环节\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of studying all the stars in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.50,0:42:49.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最终  空间探测器带来的知识将远不止于太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Ultimately, space probes will bring us knowledge far beyond the sun
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.18,0:42:51.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而是深入我们星系的偏远地带\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and into the distant parts of our galaxy,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.82,0:42:55.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在那里  数十亿太阳在燃烧\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where billions of other suns burn and potentially,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.81,0:42:59.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也许  还有几颗蓝色的星球等待着人们去探索\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a few blue planets await future human explorers.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.79,0:43:03.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为了揭开宇宙最神奇的秘密\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To learn some of the most amazing secrets about our universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.74,0:43:05.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}艾米·美因茨\N美国国家宇航局/喷气推进实验室
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.91,0:43:06.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们需要航天器的帮助  因为它们可以前往观测\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we need spacecraft because they can go places
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.37,0:43:08.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那些我们在地球上到达不了  观测不到的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and see things that we could never do from here on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.81,0:43:14.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们向宇宙发射探测器  还出于一个更深层的原因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's a deeper reason that we send probes out into space.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.18,0:43:21.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,人类骨子里流淌着求知与发现的血液\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We humans have it in our DNA to be curious and to explore.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.72,0:43:19.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}杰佛里·马尔西\N美国加州大学伯克利分校
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.29,0:43:24.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当然了  我们向太空\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and of course, probes that we send into space,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.41,0:43:27.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,向行星  以及最终向恒星发射的探测器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to the planets, and ultimately to the stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.56,0:43:31.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,代表着一颗我们向宇宙移民的心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}represent our migration into the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.14,0:43:35.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,人类作为一个整体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It is almost certainly our destiny as a species
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.57,0:43:39.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,几乎注定要驶出地球  飞入银河系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to crawl off the planet earth and out into our galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.33,0:43:41.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,走向宇宙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the universe as a whole.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.49,0:43:44.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,到那一天\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Until that day,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.85,0:43:49.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,空间探测器将会继续向我们呈现宇宙的奇观\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}space probes will continue to peel back the wonders of the cosmos,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.03,0:43:53.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些机器承载着人类探索恒星的梦想\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the universe will continue to give up her secrets,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.40,0:44:00.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙也将继续向我们展现她的秘密\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as these robotic avatars persue humanity's quest for the stars.
